INSERT INTO `language__blogs` (`id`, `language_id`, `blog_id`, `title`, `desc`, `date`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(1, '1', '1', 'What Is Specialty Coffee?', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Specialty coffee has been in trend for a long time now. But what</span><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">﻿</span><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\"> exactly makes coffee, a specialty? Let us first explore the nuances of a specialty coffee.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">The term “</span><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">specialty</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">” (often confused with speciality which literally translates to strength) was first used to refer to coffee in 1974 by Erna Knutsen in an issue of the&nbsp;</span><em style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Tea &amp; Coffee Journal</span></em><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">. The word was used to describe coffee that was produced in a microclimate with high-quality and unique flavour profiles. Today, however, the word “specialty” is everywhere in the industry. It is used relentlessly on packaging and signage, and used by baristas and roasters alike.&nbsp;But with time, the meaning and essence of specialty coffee has changed.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">In today’s coffee production ‘regular’ is often used a degraded synonym for bad quality, lack of sustainability and transparency. In return, this means that regular coffee might come with an unpleasant experience through bad taste and a not so great feeling in your body. Conversely, most cases of specialty coffee mean for guaranteed quality throughout all stages of the coffee production from process from the seed into your coffee cup.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">To understand the making of specialty coffee, let us first understand the grading system. All coffee beans are graded out of 100 under the process of “cupping”. According to the&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Specialty Coffee Association (SCA)</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">, specialty coffee is&nbsp;Arabica coffee&nbsp;with a cup score of 80+ points. But the coffee must have been cupped by a&nbsp;certified Q grader. On top of that,&nbsp;too many defects&nbsp;in a sample of the green, unroasted coffee beans will automatically disqualify that coffee from specialty status.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">But is Specialty coffee only about the beans?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Since the beans can’t have many defects, the coffee plants need to be&nbsp;carefully cultivated and harvested&nbsp;at the right time. Specialty coffee is grown by farmers in select altitudes and climates and nursed for years before the first harvest. While processing, the quality and not the quantity is the first priority. The coffee is next transferred to the green coffee buyer. They identify the coffee quality via cupping, or systematic tasting of brewed coffees. Through cupping, the coffee taster can assess a coffee’s score and determines whether it is specialty grade quality or not. High quality coffees are next transferred to the coffee roaster. Coffee must be closely monitored during the roasting process and scientific principles of heat transfer, thermodynamics and coffee chemistry must be applied to ensure the highest standard of quality and flavor come through in the final roasted bean. Next it is passed on to The Barista who ensures each bean reaches its full brewed promise.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Evolution of Specialty Coffee</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">However, despite the fact that the SCA cupping scale and the physical grading system both provide objective definitions, the definition of what specialty coffee is or rather, what it stands for, seems to have changed.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Today, the word “specialty” is often used synonymously with words like “artisan”, and is frequently associated with concepts such as transparency, traceability, and direct trade. It is also used interchangeably by some people with the concept of third wave coffee – which, unlike specialty, does not have an objective definition. Today, specialty coffee has evolved from an objective definition to encompass an ideal that caters to a “specialty coffee community”.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Best practices</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Producers must adhere to best&nbsp;processing&nbsp;practices, and&nbsp;storage protocols&nbsp;should also be followed. Therefore, storing them in</span><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">&nbsp;9 layer hermetic packaging</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">&nbsp;restores the flavor and keep the quality intact. Ecotact specializes in packaging of specialty coffee with their supreme quality multilayered hermetic coffee packaging bags</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">• Protects aroma, moisture and water activity of the specialty coffee</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">• Provides excellent transparency and is certified food safe</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">• Increases shelf life and keeps the coffee fresh for a very long duration</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">• Use of insecticide or pesticide not required for preservation</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">• High-temperature tolerance</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">• High resistance to oil and solvents</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">• Easy recyclability and&nbsp;eco-friendly structure</span></p>', '2020-12-22', '2021-04-29 11:42:05', '2021-06-22 08:01:53'),
(2, '2', '1', '¿Qué es el Café Especial?', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">El caf&eacute; de especialidad est&aacute; de moda desde hace tiempo. Pero, &iquest;qu&eacute; es exactamente lo que convierte al caf&eacute; en una especialidad? Exploremos primero los matices de un caf&eacute; de especialidad. El t&eacute;rmino \"especial\" (que a menudo se confunde con especialidad, que se traduce como fortaleza) fue utilizado por primera vez para referirse al caf&eacute; en 1974 por Erna Knutsen en un n&uacute;mero de la revista Tea &amp; Coffee Journal. La palabra se utilizaba para describir el caf&eacute; que se produc&iacute;a en un microclima con perfiles de sabor &uacute;nicos y de alta calidad. Hoy, sin embargo, la palabra \"especialidad \" est&aacute; en todas partes en la industria. Se utiliza sin cesar en los envases y la se&ntilde;alizaci&oacute;n, y la emplean tanto los baristas como los tostadores. Pero con el tiempo, el significado y la esencia del caf&eacute; especialidad ha cambiado.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Actualmente, en la producci&oacute;n de caf&eacute; el t&eacute;rmino \"regular\" se utiliza a menudo como sin&oacute;nimo de mala calidad, falta de sostenibilidad y transparencia. A su vez, esto significa que el caf&eacute; regular puede venir acompa&ntilde;ado de una experiencia desagradable por su mal sabor y una sensaci&oacute;n no muy agradable para tus sentidos. Por el contrario, en la mayor&iacute;a de los casos el caf&eacute; de especialidad significa calidad garantizada en todas las etapas de la producci&oacute;n del caf&eacute;, desde la semilla hasta su taza.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Para entender la elaboraci&oacute;n del caf&eacute; de especialidad, entendamos primero el sistema de clasificaci&oacute;n. Todos los granos de caf&eacute; se clasifican sobre 100 seg&uacute;n el proceso de \"cata\". De acuerdo a la Asociaci&oacute;n de Caf&eacute;s Especiales (SCA), el caf&eacute; especial es un caf&eacute; ar&aacute;bigo con una puntuaci&oacute;n en taza superior a 80 puntos. Pero el caf&eacute; debe haber sido catado por un catador Q certificado. Adem&aacute;s, si se encuentra demasiados defectos en una muestra de caf&eacute; verdes y sin tostar, descalifica autom&aacute;ticamente ese caf&eacute; de la categor&iacute;a de especialidad.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pero, &iquest;el caf&eacute; de especialidad se refiere s&oacute;lo a los granos?</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dado que los granos no pueden tener muchos defectos, las plantas de caf&eacute; deben ser cultivadas cuidadosamente y cosechadas en el momento adecuado. Los caf&eacute;s especiales son cultivados por los agricultores en altitudes y climas selectos y se cultivan durante a&ntilde;os, antes de la primera cosecha. En el procesamiento, se prioriza la calidad y no la cantidad. Posteriormente, el caf&eacute; se transfiere al comprador de caf&eacute; verde. Este identifica la calidad del caf&eacute; mediante la cata, o degustaci&oacute;n sistem&aacute;tica de caf&eacute;s tostados. A trav&eacute;s de la cata, el catador de caf&eacute; puede evaluar la puntuaci&oacute;n de un caf&eacute; y determinar si es de calidad especial o no. A continuaci&oacute;n, los caf&eacute;s de alta calidad se transfieren al tostador. El caf&eacute; debe ser supervisado estrechamente durante el proceso de tostado y deben aplicarse los principios cient&iacute;ficos de transferencia de calor, termodin&aacute;mica y qu&iacute;mica del caf&eacute;, a fin de garantizar finalmente el m&aacute;ximo nivel de calidad y sabor en el grano tostado. Luego, el caf&eacute; pasa a las manos del barista, quien debe asegurar que cada grano tostado alcance su m&aacute;ximo potencial.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Evoluci&oacute;n de los caf&eacute;s de especialidad</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sin embargo, a pesar de que tanto la escala de cata de la SCA como el sistema de clasificaci&oacute;n f&iacute;sica proporcionan definiciones objetivas, la definici&oacute;n de lo que es el caf&eacute; especial o, mejor dicho, lo que representa, parece haber cambiado.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hoy en d&iacute;a, la palabra \"especialidad\" se utiliza a menudo como sin&oacute;nimo de palabras como \"artesanal\", y se asocia con frecuencia a conceptos como transparencia, trazabilidad y comercio directo. Tambi&eacute;n se utiliza indistintamente por algunas personas con el concepto de caf&eacute; de tercera ola, que, a diferencia de la especialidad, no tiene una definici&oacute;n objetiva. Hoy en d&iacute;a, el caf&eacute; de especialidad ha evolucionado desde una definici&oacute;n objetiva hasta abarcar un ideal que atiende a una \"comunidad de caf&eacute;s de especialidad\".</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mejores pr&aacute;cticas</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Los productores deben incorporar mejores pr&aacute;cticas de procesamiento, y tambi&eacute;n deben seguir los protocolos de almacenamiento. Por ello, se recomienda almacenar el caf&eacute; en envases herm&eacute;ticos de 9 capas, debido a que mejora el sabor y mantiene intacta la calidad. Ecotact se especializa en el desarrollo y venta de empaques herm&eacute;ticos multicapas, bolsas de alta calidad dise&ntilde;adas para el envasado de caf&eacute;s especiales.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">- Protege el aroma, la humedad y la actividad del agua del caf&eacute; especial</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">- Proporciona una excelente visibilidad del grano y est&aacute;n certificados como empaques de grado alimenticio</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">- Prolonga la vida &uacute;til y mantiene el caf&eacute; fresco durante mucho tiempo</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">- No requiere el uso de insecticidas o pesticidas para su conservaci&oacute;n</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">- Tolerancia a las altas temperaturas</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">- Alta resistencia al aceite y a los disolventes</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">- F&aacute;cil de reciclar y estructura ecoamigable</span></p>', '2020-12-22', '2021-04-29 11:42:05', '2021-06-22 08:01:53'),
(3, '1', '2', 'Know Your Cocoa with Uncommon Cacao', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">In conversation with Uncommon Cacao member, Stasi Baranoff about the cocoa industry.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">1) Tell us more about how you ventured into the cocoa industry?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">In 2010, our Founder and CEO Emily Stone followed her love for chocolate and experience in environmental activism to set up a cocoa processing company in Southern Belize. That was the beginning of the Uncommon Cacao Group, a certified B Corp social enterprise dedicated towards improving farmer livelihoods through high quality, transparent cacao supply chains. We are a group of three companies: Maya Mountain Cacao (a processor and exporter in Belize), Cacao Verapaz (an exporter in Guatemala) and Uncommon Cacao (a broker in the US). Uncommon Cacao is a brokerage that sells beans from both of our sister companies, as well as 8 additional supply partners in 8 additional countries.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">2)&nbsp;How has the cocoa industry evolved over the past few years?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Since we started in 2010, we’ve seen a growth of interest in bean-to-bar, specialty chocolate companies that are focused on high quality, ethically sourced ingredients. Our chocolate-making customers, and their consumer customers, expect a consistency in the product with an impactful story, whether that’s social, environmental, or economic impact. In the past, consumers and traders thought of cocoa and chocolate as a fungible and cheap commodity. These days, people in the industry understand that different qualities of cacao deserve different prices and that specialty chocolate maker and consumers shouldn’t think of cacao as a commodity at all.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">3) What are the best practices of producing quality cocoa?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Consistency is key. Chocolate makers seek consistency, with the same quality and flavor from harvest to harvest. In order to achieve this, producer groups, or processing companies, need to follow processing protocols to ferment and dry cocoa beans. The usual process involves these steps:</span></p><ol style=\"margin: 23px 0px 34px 40px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; list-style: none; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); counter-reset: item 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Good agronomic practices to maintain tree and pod health, to maximize yield and ensure mature pods.</span></li><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Harvesting only the ripe cocoa pods, that have a high enough BRIX (or sugar) content to ferment</span></li><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Combining enough volume of cocoa pulp and beans in fermentation boxes to have a critical mass of juices and sugars for the fermentation process to be successful.</span></li><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Conducting both anaerobic and aerobic fermentation, for a span of 4-8 days depending on the location, type of cocoa, and volume of fermenting cacao</span></li><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Two stages of drying; a slow drying process, usually covered and on mesh tables, and fast drying, usually in direct sunlight on a patio, raked frequently throughout</span></li><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Sorting, by hand if possible, to ensure that only whole cacao beans are packed into the bags for export.</span></li></ol><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">4) What makes the different variety of cocoa unique from each other?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">There are hundreds, if not thousands, of cocoa varieties due to the ease with which cocoa can be cross-bred. However, generally speaking there are considered to be four familial groups: Criollo, Amelonado, Forastero, and Trinitario. These are different not only in shape and native growing regions, but also in general flavor notes.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">5)&nbsp;How do you preserve your cocoa produce? How important are good hermetic Packaging solutions to your business and are there any specific brands that you prefer?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Cacao is generally stored in large sacks – polypropylene or jute/sisal. These sacks are stored on pallets inside warehouses. Because cacao is sensitive to odour, and is intentionally dried to a very specific humidity level, hermetic packaging is essential for a high quality product. Our company uses Ecotact which serves the purpose of preservation of humidity and protection from odour.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">6) Have you noticed a change in the consumption pattern/demand of Cocoa during the Pandemic?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Specialty or Fine Flavor cocoa has maintained its consumption patterns, and craft chocolate has been resilient for the most part. We saw a reduction in demand over the summer months for cocoa beans, but as the holiday season starts, demand is picking back up as our customers make chocolate for the holidays.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">7) How do you think hermetic packaging is helping the cocoa industry in these difficult times?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Reliable, clean storage is essential during this time. As purchasing slows, the cocoa needs to maintain its humidity and quality. As a company, we decided to continue operations, and stick to our original purchase commitments with each of our cocoa suppliers. We knew that cocoa is most stable in its fermented and dried state, packed in hermetically sealed bags, and least stable as a fruit on the tree. If a farmer were to leave the fruit on the tree to rot, inevitably their future harvests would suffer due to disease that can easily spread when trees are not maintained. We knew that if income were still flowing to farmers, plots would be maintained and would be more disease resistant for future harvests. As a result, we made sure to keep our commitments, and with cocoa packed in Ecotact bags in a US warehouse, we know we can keep this cocoa in good quality for months and potentially years to come.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">8) Has the pandemic affected the cocoa industry adversely?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">It seems to have affected different cacao growing and consuming regions differently, so it’s hard to say with a blanket statement that it has affected the whole industry adversely. Luckily, for the most part, cocoa growing regions seem to be only mildly affected by the pandemic in terms of health in the regions. Rural farming communities are more spread out, and so COVID does not seem to be spreading as widely. This means that farmers are healthy and able to tend to farms.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">9) Preferred moisture levels she prefers to pack the cocoa into Ecotact bags?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Cocoa needs to be at a humidity level less than 7.5% – ideally in the 6-7.5% range. This is to prevent the growth of mold both on the outside and on the inside of the beans. Therefore, our suppliers pack their cocoa in hermetically sealed bags at a humidity level in this range, to keep its stability and flavor.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">10) Do you use Ecotact bags for storage in warehouse also or only for exports ?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">We keep cocoa stored in Ecotact bags both in the country of origin as well as in the warehouses in the US. There are a number of risks that cocoa can come into contact with both in origin warehouses and in destination warehouses: odors, humid climates, cocoa moths, and so we try to do everything we can to preserve the quality. This includes keeping cocoa stored in Ecotact bags.</span></p>', '2020-11-26', '2021-04-29 11:43:16', '2021-06-22 08:03:20'),
(4, '2', '2', 'Conoce Tu Cacao Con Uncommon Cacao', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">En conversaci&oacute;n con un miembro de Uncommon Cacao - Stasi Baranoff, sobre la industria del cacao.</span></p>\r\n    <ul>\r\n    <li aria-level=\"1\"><strong>Cu&eacute;ntenos m&aacute;s sobre c&oacute;mo se aventur&oacute; en la industria del cacao.</strong></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">En 2010, nuestra fundadora &amp; CEO- Emily Stone, sigui&oacute; su amor por el chocolate y su experiencia en el activismo medioambiental para crear una empresa de procesamiento de cacao en el sur de Belice. Ese fue el comienzo del Grupo Uncommon Cacao, una empresa social con certificaci&oacute;n B Corp dedicada a mejorar los medios de vida de los agricultores a trav&eacute;s de cadenas de suministro de cacao transparentes y de alta calidad. Somos un grupo de tres empresas: Maya Mountain Cacao (un procesador y exportador en Belice), Cacao Verapaz (un exportador en Guatemala) y Uncommon Cacao (un intermediario en Estados Unidos). Uncommon Cacao es un intermediario que vende granos de nuestras dos empresas hermanas, as&iacute; como de otros 8 socios proveedores en otros 8 pa&iacute;ses.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><strong>2) &iquest;C&oacute;mo ha evolucionado la industria del cacao en los &uacute;ltimos a&ntilde;os?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Desde que empezamos en el 2010, hemos observado un aumento del inter&eacute;s por las empresas de chocolate especializadas que se centran en ingredientes de alta calidad y de origen &eacute;tico. Nuestros clientes chocolateros, y sus clientes consumidores, esperan una consistencia en el producto con una historia impactante, ya sea un impacto social, medioambiental o econ&oacute;mico. En el pasado, los consumidores y los comerciantes consideraban el cacao y el chocolate como una mercanc&iacute;a fungible y barata. Hoy en d&iacute;a, la gente del sector entiende que las distintas calidades de cacao merecen precios diferentes y que los chocolateros y los consumidores no deber&iacute;an pensar en el cacao como una mercanc&iacute;a en absoluto.</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><strong>3) &iquest;Cu&aacute;les son las mejores pr&aacute;cticas para producir un cacao de calidad?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">La consistencia es la clave. Los chocolateros buscan la consistencia, con la misma calidad y sabor de una cosecha a otra. Para conseguirlo, los grupos de productores, o las empresas de transformaci&oacute;n, deben seguir protocolos de procesamiento para fermentar y secar los granos de cacao. El proceso habitual incluye estos pasos:</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br /><br /></span></p>\r\n    <ol>\r\n    <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Buenas pr&aacute;cticas agron&oacute;micas para mantener la salud de los &aacute;rboles y las mazorcas, para maximizar el rendimiento y asegurar la madurez de las mazorcas.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cosechar s&oacute;lo las mazorcas de cacao maduras, que tengan un grado BRIX (az&uacute;cares) lo suficientemente alto como para poder fermentar</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Colectar un volumen suficiente de pulpa de cacao y colocarlos en los cajones de fermentaci&oacute;n, para que los altos niveles de az&uacute;cares y &aacute;cidos que contiene la pulpa creen las condiciones ideales para tener &eacute;xito en el proceso de fermentaci&oacute;n.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Llevar a cabo una fermentaci&oacute;n tanto anaer&oacute;bica como aer&oacute;bica, durante un lapso de 4 a 8 d&iacute;as, dependiendo de la ubicaci&oacute;n, el tipo de cacao y el volumen de cacao a fermentar.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Realizar el proceso de secado en dos etapas; un proceso de secado lento, normalmente cubierto y sobre mesas de malla, y un secado r&aacute;pido al sol, en un patio, rastrillando frecuentemente durante todo el proceso</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Clasificar el cacao a mano si es posible, para garantizar que s&oacute;lo los granos de cacao enteros se introduzcan en los sacos para la exportaci&oacute;n.</span></li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><strong>4) &iquest;Qu&eacute; hace que las distintas variedades de cacao sean &uacute;nicas entre s&iacute;?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">No hay cientos, sino miles de variedades de cacao, debido a la facilidad con la que se puede cruzar el cacao. Sin embargo, en t&eacute;rminos generales se considera que hay cuatro grupos familiares: Criollo, Amelonado, Forastero y Trinitario. Estas variedades se diferencian no s&oacute;lo por su forma y sus regiones de cultivo, sino tambi&eacute;n por sus notas de sabor generales.</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><strong>5) &iquest;C&oacute;mo conserva sus productos de cacao? &iquest;Qu&eacute; importancia tienen las buenas soluciones de envasado herm&eacute;tico para su negocio y hay alguna marca espec&iacute;fica que prefiera?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">El cacao se almacena generalmente en grandes sacos de polipropileno o yute/sisal. Estos sacos se almacenan en palets dentro de los almacenes. Dado que el cacao es sensible a los olores y se seca intencionadamente a un nivel de humedad muy espec&iacute;fico, el envasado herm&eacute;tico es esencial para obtener un producto de alta calidad. Nuestra empresa utiliza Ecotact, porque sirve para preservar la humedad y proteger del olor.</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><strong>6) &iquest;Ha notado un cambio en el patr&oacute;n de consumo/demanda de cacao durante la pandemia?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">El cacao de especialidad o fino de sabor, ha mantenido sus patrones de consumo, y el chocolate artesanal ha resistido en su mayor parte. Hemos observado una reducci&oacute;n de la demanda de cacao en grano durante los meses de verano, pero con el comienzo de la temporada de vacaciones, la demanda est&aacute; volviendo a aumentar a medida que nuestros clientes elaboran chocolate para las fiestas de la temporada de vacaciones.</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><strong>7) &iquest;C&oacute;mo cree que los envases herm&eacute;ticos est&aacute;n ayudando a la industria del cacao en estos tiempos dif&iacute;ciles?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Un almacenamiento confiable y limpio es esencial en esta &eacute;poca. Al disminuir las compras, el cacao necesita mantener su humedad y calidad. Como empresa, decidimos seguir operando y mantener nuestros compromisos de compra originales con cada uno de nuestros proveedores de cacao. Sab&iacute;amos que el cacao es m&aacute;s estable en su estado fermentado y seco, y se conserva mejor envasado en bolsas herm&eacute;ticas. Si un agricultor dejara que el fruto se pudriera en el &aacute;rbol, inevitablemente sus futuras cosechas se ver&iacute;an afectadas por las enfermedades que pueden propagarse f&aacute;cilmente cuando los &aacute;rboles no se mantienen. Sab&iacute;amos que, si los ingresos segu&iacute;an llegando a los agricultores, las parcelas se mantendr&iacute;an y ser&iacute;an m&aacute;s resistentes a las enfermedades para futuras cosechas. En consecuencia, nos aseguramos de cumplir nuestros compromisos, y con el cacao empacado en bolsas Ecotact en un almac&eacute;n estadounidense, sabemos que podemos mantener este cacao en buena calidad durante meses y potencialmente a&ntilde;os.</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><strong>8) &iquest;Ha afectado la pandemia negativamente a la industria del cacao?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Parece haber afectado de forma diferente a las distintas regiones productoras y consumidoras de cacao, por lo que es dif&iacute;cil afirmar de forma general que ha afectado negativamente a toda la industria. Por suerte, en su mayor parte, las regiones productoras de cacao parecen estar levemente afectadas por la pandemia en t&eacute;rminos de salud en las regiones. Las comunidades agr&iacute;colas rurales est&aacute;n m&aacute;s repartidas, por lo que el COVID no parece extenderse tanto. Esto significa que los agricultores est&aacute;n sanos y son capaces de atender sus fincas.</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><strong>9) &iquest;Qu&eacute; Niveles de humedad prefiere para envasar el cacao en bolsas Ecotact?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">El cacao debe tener un nivel de humedad inferior al 7,5%, idealmente entre el 6 y el 7,5%. Esto es para evitar el crecimiento de moho tanto en el exterior como en el interior de los granos. Por lo tanto, nuestros proveedores envasan su cacao en bolsas herm&eacute;ticas con un nivel de humedad en este rango, para mantener su estabilidad y sabor.</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><strong>10) &iquest;Utilizan las bolsas Ecotact tambi&eacute;n para el almacenamiento en el almac&eacute;n o s&oacute;lo para la exportaci&oacute;n?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mantenemos el cacao almacenado en bolsas Ecotact tanto en el pa&iacute;s de origen como en los almacenes de Estados Unidos. Tanto en los almacenes de origen como en los de destino, el cacao puede entrar en contacto con una serie de riesgos: olores, climas h&uacute;medos, polillas del cacao, por lo que intentamos hacer todo lo posible para preservar la calidad. Esto incluye mantener el cacao almacenado en bolsas Ecotact.</span></p>', '2020-11-26', '2021-04-29 11:43:16', '2021-06-22 08:03:20');
