(5, '1', '3', 'Coffee Fermentation and Their Processes', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Curious about knowing coffee fermentation and what differentiates cultured coffee from the rest? It’s time to quench your brewing curiosity. Let us first understand the basics of fermentation.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Fermentation is a chemical reaction. The combination of yeast, bacteria, and other microorganisms causes a substance to break down into other simpler substances. Normally, the substances that get broken down are sugars. As this happens, they tend to release heat. Also, different kinds of enzymes can catalyze this event.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Or, to put it more simply, fermentation is a natural change that happens when you put sugar and water together – and coffee cherries are full of both. And so, just after the cherries are picked (or sometimes before, depending on the humidity), the fermentation process will start.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Fermentation is a key part of post-harvest coffee processing. It can happen in one of two ways:</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Aerobic:</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">This is what happens when oxygen is available. Engineering this kind of fermentation is simple. For the washed coffee production, the time period when pulped coffee is macerated&nbsp;—&nbsp;usually in open-air tanks or buckets or now&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">in food-safe Ecotact hermetic bags</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">, the process is known as aerobic fermentation. It is a traditional method of fermenting and farmers use this method for removing the sticky fruit mucilage from the parchment-covered coffee seed. The changing flavor although important, is most of the times secondary to getting rid of the fruit sugars and pectin. The time period allocated for aerobic fermentation is 12-24 hours. If the temperature is heightened, fermenting for 12 hours suffices.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Anaerobic:</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">In general, anaerobic means oxygen-free. When coffee farmers use this word, they usually mean they’ve created a sealed environment.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Now let us understand the process of fermentation in an Ecotact bag.</span></p><ul style=\"margin: 23px 0px 34px 40px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; list-style: none;\"><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><font color=\"#222222\" face=\"Merriweather, serif\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-style: inherit; font-variant-ligatures: inherit; font-variant-caps: inherit; font-weight: inherit;\">Typically the coffee is pulped as usual and then the beans with mucilage&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 18px; font-style: inherit; font-variant-ligatures: inherit; font-variant-caps: inherit; font-weight: inherit;\">the parchment with mucilage is placed into hermetically-sealed airtight food-safe Ecotact plastic bags with a valve to allow for off-gassing.</span></font></li><li style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Merriweather, serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Place the Ecotact bags in cold water to avoid bacteria.</span></li><li style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Merriweather, serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">As the fermentation begins the levels of Oxygen diminish and the Carbon dioxide increase, creating pressure in the strong expandable airtight&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://www.ecotactbags.com/eco-products/packaging\" style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; color: rgb(17, 102, 54); display: inline-block;\" target=\"_blank\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Ecotact bags</span></strong></a></li><li style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Merriweather, serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">This style of fermentation may extend the traditional timeframe of 12-24 hours by hours or even days in some cases and long enough for the mucilage to be consumed, but not so long that alcohol is produced.</span></li><li style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Merriweather, serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">After 12 hours the pH needs to be constantly checked or controlled to determine how the fermentation is progressing. Measuring the Brix of the coffee from time to time may help too.</span></li><li style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Merriweather, serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Typically, the fermentation process can be stopped when Brix drops to 16 °Bx.&nbsp;The pressure created by the carbon dioxide allows the flavours of the coffee juices to be injected into the parchment. Once the fermentation has concluded the Ecotact bags are opened carefully.</span></li><li style=\"color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Merriweather, serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">The coffee is then sun dried for at least 4 hours, otherwise the fermentation might continue and the flavors may change.</span></li></ul><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">So, what’s the difference? The anaerobic processes are more homogeneous and easier to monitor, and the aerobics are more heterogeneous and more complex to monitor.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Also keep a note to assess the behavior of the beans under the given environmental conditions like temperature, coffee variety, humidity, pH, homogenous harvesting etc.!</span></p><h2 style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: 30px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); letter-spacing: normal;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">A Word of Caution</span></strong></h2><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Anaerobic fermentation of coffee is just one of a number of interesting innovations occurring on forward-thinking farms. These types of progressive and experimental practices can encourage creativity in an industry frequently reliant on tradition, and provide market differentiation for producers seeking liberation from C-market prices.</span></p>', '2020-11-04', '2021-04-29 11:44:20', '2021-07-30 08:40:02'),
(6, '2', '3', 'La Fermentación del Café y Sus Procesos', '<p><strong>&iquest;Tiene curiosidad por conocer la fermentaci&oacute;n del caf&eacute; y lo que diferencia al caf&eacute; cultivado del resto?</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Es hora de saciar su curiosidad. Entendamos primero los fundamentos de la fermentaci&oacute;n.</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">La fermentaci&oacute;n es una reacci&oacute;n qu&iacute;mica. La combinaci&oacute;n de levaduras, bacterias y otros microorganismos hace que una sustancia se descomponga en otras m&aacute;s simples. Normalmente, las sustancias que se descomponen son az&uacute;cares. Cuando esto ocurre, tienden a liberar calor. Adem&aacute;s, diferentes tipos de enzimas pueden catalizar este acontecimiento.</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">O, para decirlo de forma m&aacute;s sencilla, la fermentaci&oacute;n es un cambio natural que se produce cuando se juntan el az&uacute;car y el agua, y las cerezas del caf&eacute; est&aacute;n llenas de ambos. Y as&iacute;, justo despu&eacute;s de recoger las cerezas (o a veces antes, seg&uacute;n la humedad), comenzar&aacute; el proceso de fermentaci&oacute;n.</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">La fermentaci&oacute;n es una parte fundamental del procesamiento del caf&eacute; despu&eacute;s de la cosecha. Puede ocurrir de dos maneras:</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Aer&oacute;bica: es la que ocurre cuando hay ox&iacute;geno disponible. La ingenier&iacute;a de este tipo de fermentaci&oacute;n es sencilla. Para la producci&oacute;n de caf&eacute; lavado, el per&iacute;odo de tiempo en el que el caf&eacute; despulpado se macera generalmente en tanques de fermentaci&oacute;n al aire libre o ahora tambi&eacute;n en bolsas herm&eacute;ticas Ecotact aptas para alimentos, el proceso se conoce como fermentaci&oacute;n aer&oacute;bica. Es un m&eacute;todo tradicional de fermentaci&oacute;n y los agricultores lo utilizan para eliminar el muc&iacute;lago de la fruta de la semilla de caf&eacute; cubierta de pergamino. El cambio de sabor, aunque importante, es la mayor&iacute;a de las veces secundario a la eliminaci&oacute;n de los az&uacute;cares de la fruta y la pectina. El per&iacute;odo de tiempo asignado para la fermentaci&oacute;n aer&oacute;bica es de 12 a 24 horas. Si la temperatura es elevada, basta con fermentar durante 12 horas.</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Anaer&oacute;bico: en general, anaer&oacute;bico significa libre de ox&iacute;geno. Cuando los caficultores utilizan esta palabra, suelen significar que han creado un entorno sellado.</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ahora entendamos el proceso de fermentaci&oacute;n en una bolsa Ecotact.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><br /><br /></span></p>\r\n    <ul>\r\n    <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Granos con mucílago se coloca en bolsas de pl&aacute;stico Ecotact herm&eacute;ticas con una v&aacute;lvula para permitir la desgasificaci&oacute;n.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Coloque las bolsas Ecotact en agua fr&iacute;a para evitar las bacterias.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A medida que se inicia la fermentaci&oacute;n, los niveles de ox&iacute;geno disminuyen y el di&oacute;xido de carbono aumenta, lo que crea una presi&oacute;n en las resistentes bolsas Ecotact herm&eacute;ticas expandibles.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Este estilo de fermentaci&oacute;n puede alargar el plazo tradicional de 12-24 horas en horas o incluso d&iacute;as en algunos casos y lo suficiente como para que se consuma el muc&iacute;lago, pero no tanto como para que se produzca alcohol.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Despu&eacute;s de 12 horas es necesario comprobar o controlar constantemente el pH para determinar c&oacute;mo progresa la fermentaci&oacute;n. Medir los grados Brix del caf&eacute; de vez en cuando tambi&eacute;n puede ayudar.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Normalmente, el proceso de fermentaci&oacute;n puede detenerse cuando los grados Brix bajan a 16 &deg;Bx. La presi&oacute;n creada por el di&oacute;xido de carbono permite que los sabores de los jugos del caf&eacute; se inyecten en el pergamino. Una vez concluida la fermentaci&oacute;n, los sacos Ecotact se abren con cuidado.</span></li>\r\n    <li style=\"font-weight: 400;\" aria-level=\"1\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A continuaci&oacute;n, el caf&eacute; se seca al sol durante al menos 4 horas, ya que de lo contrario la fermentaci&oacute;n podr&iacute;a continuar y los sabores podr&iacute;an cambiar.</span></li>\r\n    </ul>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Entonces, &iquest;cu&aacute;l es la diferencia? Los procesos anaer&oacute;bicos son m&aacute;s homog&eacute;neos y m&aacute;s f&aacute;ciles de controlar, y los aer&oacute;bicos son m&aacute;s heterog&eacute;neos y m&aacute;s complejos de controlar.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Para evaluar el comportamiento de los granos en las condiciones ambientales dadas, tambi&eacute;n es necesario tomar en cuenta otras variables como: la temperatura, la variedad de caf&eacute;, la humedad, el pH, ver si la cosecha es homog&eacute;nea, etc.</span></p>\r\n    <p><strong>Consideraciones a tener en cuenta</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">La fermentaci&oacute;n anaer&oacute;bica del caf&eacute; es s&oacute;lo una de las interesantes innovaciones que se producen en las fincas que cuentan con visi&oacute;n de futuro. Este tipo de pr&aacute;cticas progresistas y experimentales pueden fomentar la creatividad en un sector que suele depender de la tradici&oacute;n, y proporcionar una diferenciaci&oacute;n de mercado a los productores que buscan liberarse de los precios del mercado C.</span></p>', '2020-11-04', '2021-04-29 11:44:20', '2021-07-30 08:40:02'),
(7, '1', '4', 'Exploring Specialty Coffee', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">In an exciting conversation with&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Arnaud Causse, CEO Las Tolas Estate Coffee</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">,</span><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">&nbsp;Ecuador</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">&nbsp;we explore the production of specialty coffee and the popularity of it.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">1) Tell us more about how you ventured into the specialty coffee industry.</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">&nbsp;During a long mission in El Salvador after the Peace Accords, I discovered that certain coffees could be valued in niche markets that were beginning to differentiate the coffees.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">While I was looking to improve the quality and fame of the Galapagos coffee, I decided to find the ideal place to produce a highly differentiated coffee, based on my experiences around the world applying the principle of “layers” on a map. This is how project Las Tolas Estate was born in the Northwest of Pichincha. The reception as soon as we started production was very encouraging surfing on the 3rd wave at its beginning.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">2) What inspired you to experiment with different coffee growing techniques? Please share a little about them. How do these processes distinguish your coffee?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">The inspiration comes from the accumulation of experiences and exchanges with a multitude of producers passionate about Africa, Central America, the Caribbean and South America. To this is added the permanent observation of the behavior of the coffee plantations of Las Tolas and Terrazas del Pisque and the results of the tastings.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">The agro-ecological management that we implement is giving surprising results both in productivity and in the generation of aroma precursors. With these techniques we can guarantee an optimal intrinsic quality of our coffee (s) that we sublimate and then atomize through various post-harvest processes to constitute a full range of potential expression.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">3) How has Cider coffee gained recognition in recent years and how will it remain in the coming years, according to you?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Sidra coffee has gained much fame for its excellent behavior in the cup; however, its genetic “footprint” is not yet defined and therefore the variation is uncontrollable. I think that the only conclusion that would be sustainable is that the crossing between Bourbones and certain heirlooms originating from Ethiopian germplasm allows the development of very promising populations under certain particular conditions.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Sidra</span><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">, eat Geisha, will have its glory years until a new family of cultivars appears with characteristics more adapted to market expectations or until consumers change their preferences.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">4) Your work has continued to evolve to the wider coffee growing community. Can you share some inspiring stories about the same?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">In the Northwest of Pichincha we were the pioneers in the cultivation of specialty coffees in a non-coffee producing area (The first crops of Las Tolas Estate are from 1999). Today there are more than 200 producers in this area who came betting on the cultivation. We have released the first material with which we began the experiments.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Today, we continue to investigate (“soft” techniques), observe (agroforestry concepts) and innovate (controlled fermentations) to share these experiences with the coffee community. Obviously I include in this community the whole of the chain even the baristas who do not rest to educate consumers and put tremendous pressure on us (producers) not to stop proposing new trends. Thus, the world of specialty coffees was tremendously energized to such an extent that, today, it is totally disconnected from “bulk” and handling “commodities”.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">5) What are the best practices for producing quality coffee?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">The best practice is undoubtedly OBSERVATION. Most growers know the cultivation manuals by heart; However, they do not apply the set of the recommended technical itinerary because they must compose with a series of own limitations inherent to the conditions of their plantations and their economies. For this reason, the most efficient are those that best knew how to adapt to both the environment and the market.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">6) How do you preserve your coffee products? How important are good hermetic packaging solutions to your business? Are there specific brands you prefer?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Our coffees are preserved on the farm both in parchment and in dry cherry in Ecotact covers to allow better homogenization (equivalent to a rest in large hoppers) and avoid contamination (fungi, mold, insects) and humidity variations. In natural coffees, the possibility of storing several months without sudden changes in conditions allows a tremendous bonus type aging. Today, I do not believe that some specialty coffee buyer does not demand that it be exported in airtight cases. Vacuum packaging, abandoned for a time, seems to be convincing again and could be an opportunity to lower the unit content even further (from 69 Kg we go to 60 Kg, then 50 Kg and 25 Kg in textile bags) below 20 Kg ( 5-10-15 Kg vacuum packs can match the batches of the small roasters’ equipment, encouraging them to buy more expensive coffees in smaller quantities.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">7) Have you noticed a change in the pattern of coffee consumption / demand during the pandemic?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Interestingly, our customers told us that the most expensive coffees sold very well. In consumer countries, this effect is due to several factors, mainly evident during confinement:</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">– Consumers had more time to research and learn about specialty coffees; So the choice of coffee went through a more in-depth selection process than usual;</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">– Consumers asked more for their coffees online and were able to access a much wider offer than in a supermarket, discovering the very advanced traceability options;</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">– Consumers saved money by not consuming outside the home and did not hesitate to pay more for their coffees and give more importance to quality;</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">8) What are some of the challenges you have faced as a specialty coffee producer due to the pandemic?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">In the midst of what must have been a true tragedy for many people, we can consider ourselves privileged in our activity and business; we don’t stop producing, we don’t stop selling.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Things got quite complicated in the administrative procedures and funding sources dried up, making economic management very difficult. At this time, the support of our allies further down the chain was crucial.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">9) How do you think airtight packaging is helping the coffee industry in these difficult times?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">I do not believe that it has a significant technical influence on health safety due to storage times and extreme precautions taken on the farms but, without a doubt, it should reassure people who must handle the product at destination.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">On the other hand, as the deadlines for all procedures have been extended, being able to preserve the coffee in better conditions is essential and producers should seriously think about using hermetic containers in farm conservation and not only as a market requirement for exports.</span></p>', '2020-10-12', '2021-04-29 11:46:15', '2021-08-19 19:15:22'),
(8, '2', '4', 'Explorando el Café de Especialidad', '<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">En una emocionante conversaci&oacute;n con Arnaud Causse - CEO de Las Tolas Estate Coffee - Ecuador, exploramos la producci&oacute;n del caf&eacute; de especialidad y su popularidad.</span></p>\r\n    <p><strong>1) Cu&eacute;ntenos m&aacute;s sobre c&oacute;mo se aventur&oacute; en la industria de los caf&eacute;s especiales.</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&nbsp;Durante una larga misi&oacute;n en El Salvador, despu&eacute;s de los Acuerdos de Paz, descubr&iacute; que ciertos caf&eacute;s pod&iacute;an ser valorados en nichos de mercado que comenzaban a diferenciarse.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mientras buscaba mejorar la calidad y la fama del caf&eacute; de Gal&aacute;pagos, decid&iacute; encontrar el lugar ideal para producir un caf&eacute; altamente diferenciado, bas&aacute;ndome en mis experiencias alrededor del mundo aplicando el principio de las \"capas\" en un mapa. As&iacute; naci&oacute; el proyecto Finca Las Tolas en el noroeste de Pichincha. La recepci&oacute;n apenas comenzamos la producci&oacute;n fue muy alentadora surfeando en la tercera ola en su inicio.</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><strong>2) &iquest;Qu&eacute; le inspir&oacute; a experimentar con diferentes t&eacute;cnicas de cultivo de caf&eacute;? Por favor, comparta un poco sobre ellas. &iquest;C&oacute;mo distinguen estos procesos a su caf&eacute;?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">La inspiraci&oacute;n proviene de la acumulaci&oacute;n de experiencias e intercambios con multitud de productores apasionados de &Aacute;frica, Centroam&eacute;rica, el Caribe y Sudam&eacute;rica. A esto se suma la observaci&oacute;n permanente del comportamiento de los cafetales de Las Tolas y Terrazas del Pisque y los resultados de las catas.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">El manejo agroecol&oacute;gico que implementamos est&aacute; dando resultados sorprendentes tanto en la productividad como en la generaci&oacute;n de precursores del aroma. Con estas t&eacute;cnicas podemos garantizar una &oacute;ptima calidad intr&iacute;nseca de nuestro(s) caf&eacute;(s) que sublimamos y luego atomizamos a trav&eacute;s de diversos procesos de post-cosecha para constituir toda una amplia gama de caf&eacute;s con expresiones potenciales.</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><strong>3) &iquest;C&oacute;mo ha ganado reconocimiento el caf&eacute; Sidra en los &uacute;ltimos a&ntilde;os y c&oacute;mo seguir&aacute; en los pr&oacute;ximos, seg&uacute;n usted?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">El caf&eacute; Sidra ha ganado mucha fama por su excelente comportamiento en la taza; sin embargo, su \"huella\" gen&eacute;tica a&uacute;n no est&aacute; definida y por lo tanto la variaci&oacute;n es incontrolable. Creo que la &uacute;nica conclusi&oacute;n sostenible es que el cruce entre Bourbones y ciertas reliquias procedentes del germoplasma et&iacute;ope permite el desarrollo de poblaciones muy prometedoras en ciertas condiciones particulares.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">La sidra, como la Geisha, tendr&aacute; sus a&ntilde;os de gloria hasta que aparezca una nueva familia de cultivares con caracter&iacute;sticas m&aacute;s adaptadas a las expectativas del mercado o hasta que los consumidores cambien sus preferencias.</span></p>\r\n    <p><strong>4) Su trabajo ha seguido evolucionando hacia la comunidad cafetera en general. &iquest;Puede compartir algunas historias inspiradoras al respecto?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">En el noroeste de Pichincha fuimos los pioneros en el cultivo de caf&eacute;s especiales en una zona no productora de caf&eacute; (Las primeras cosechas de la finca Las Tolas son de 1999). Hoy existen m&aacute;s de 200 productores en esta zona que vinieron apostando por el cultivo. Hemos sacado el primer material con el que empezamos los experimentos.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hoy seguimos investigando (t&eacute;cnicas \"suaves\"), observando (conceptos agroforestales) e innovando (fermentaciones controladas) para compartir estas experiencias con la comunidad cafetera. Obviamente, incluyo en esta comunidad a toda la cadena, incluso a los baristas, que no descansan para educar a los consumidores y ejercen una enorme presi&oacute;n sobre nosotros (los productores) para que no dejemos de proponer nuevas tendencias. As&iacute;, el mundo de los caf&eacute;s especiales se dinamiz&oacute; tremendamente hasta el punto de que, hoy en d&iacute;a, est&aacute; totalmente desvinculado del \"granel\" y del manejo de los &ldquo;commodities&rdquo;.</span></p>\r\n    <p><strong>5) &iquest;Cu&aacute;les son las mejores pr&aacute;cticas para producir un caf&eacute; de calidad?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">La mejor pr&aacute;ctica es sin duda la OBSERVACI&Oacute;N. La mayor&iacute;a de los productores saben de memoria los manuales de cultivo; sin embargo, no aplican toda la parte t&eacute;cnica que les recomienda porque deben enfrentar una serie de limitaciones propias, inherentes a las condiciones de sus plantaciones y sus econom&iacute;as. Por ello, los m&aacute;s eficientes son los que mejor han sabido adaptarse tanto al entorno como al mercado.</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><strong>6) &iquest;C&oacute;mo conserva sus caf&eacute;s? &iquest;Qu&eacute; importancia tienen las buenas soluciones de envasado herm&eacute;tico para su negocio? &iquest;Hay marcas espec&iacute;ficas que prefiera?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Nuestros caf&eacute;s se conservan en la finca tanto en pergamino como en cereza seca en bolsas Ecotact para permitir una mejor homogenizaci&oacute;n (que equivalente a un reposo en grandes tolvas) y evitar contaminaciones (hongos, moho, insectos) y variaciones de humedad. En los caf&eacute;s naturales, la posibilidad de almacenar varios meses sin cambios bruscos de condiciones permite un tremendo plus de envejecimiento tipo. Hoy en d&iacute;a, no creo que alg&uacute;n comprador de caf&eacute;s especiales no exija que se exporten en empaques herm&eacute;ticos. El envasado al vac&iacute;o, abandonado durante un tiempo, parece volver a convencer y podr&iacute;a ser una oportunidad para bajar a&uacute;n m&aacute;s el contenido unitario (de sacos de 69 Kg pasamos a 60 Kg, luego a 50 Kg y 25 Kg.) por debajo de los 20 Kg (los envases al vac&iacute;o de capacidad para 5-10-15, Kg pueden adecuarse a capacidad de los equipos de los peque&ntilde;os tostadores, anim&aacute;ndoles a comprar caf&eacute;s m&aacute;s caros en cantidades m&aacute;s peque&ntilde;as.</span></p>\r\n    <p><strong>7) &iquest;Han notado alg&uacute;n cambio en el patr&oacute;n de consumo/demanda de caf&eacute; durante la pandemia?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Curiosamente, nuestros clientes nos han dicho que los caf&eacute;s m&aacute;s caros se han vendido muy bien. En los pa&iacute;ses consumidores, este efecto se debe a varios factores, principalmente evidentes durante el confinamiento:</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">- Los consumidores tuvieron m&aacute;s tiempo para investigar y conocer acerca de los caf&eacute;s especiales; por lo que la elecci&oacute;n del caf&eacute; pas&oacute; por un proceso de selecci&oacute;n m&aacute;s profundo que el habitual;</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">- Los consumidores preguntaron m&aacute;s por sus caf&eacute;s en l&iacute;nea y pudieron acceder a una oferta mucho m&aacute;s amplia que en un supermercado, descubriendo las opciones de trazabilidad tan avanzadas;</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">- Los consumidores ahorraron dinero al no consumir fuera de casa y no dudaron en pagar m&aacute;s por sus caf&eacute;s y dar m&aacute;s importancia a la calidad;</span></p>\r\n    <p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n    <p><strong>8) &iquest;Cu&aacute;les son algunos de los retos a los que se han enfrentado como productores de caf&eacute;s especiales debido a la pandemia?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">En medio de lo que debi&oacute; ser una verdadera tragedia para muchas personas, podemos considerarnos privilegiados en nuestra actividad y negocio; no dejamos de producir, no dejamos de vender.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Las cosas se complicaron bastante en los tr&aacute;mites administrativos y las fuentes de financiaci&oacute;n se secaron, lo que hizo muy dif&iacute;cil la gesti&oacute;n econ&oacute;mica. En ese momento, el apoyo de nuestros aliados del nivel de m&aacute;s abajo en la cadena fue crucial.</span></p>\r\n    <p><strong>9) &iquest;C&oacute;mo cree que el envasado herm&eacute;tico ayuda al sector del caf&eacute; en estos tiempos dif&iacute;ciles?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">No creo que tenga una influencia t&eacute;cnica significativa en la seguridad sanitaria debido a los tiempos de almacenamiento y a las extremas precauciones que se toman en las fincas, pero, sin duda, debe tranquilizar a las personas que deben manipular el producto en destino.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Por otro lado, al ampliarse los plazos de todos los tr&aacute;mites, poder conservar el caf&eacute; en mejores condiciones es fundamental y los productores deber&iacute;an pensar seriamente en utilizar envases herm&eacute;ticos en la conservaci&oacute;n en finca y no s&oacute;lo como una exigencia del mercado para la exportaci&oacute;n.</span></p>', '2020-10-12', '2021-04-29 11:46:15', '2021-08-19 19:15:22');
