(19, '1', '10', 'Industry Insights from Samuel Coto', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">What is the global scenario of coffee plantation?</span></strong><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">In general terms the price of coffee is still the biggest challenge. However, this affects different type of producers in different ways. With the threat of COVID 19 it is hard to tell exactly what is going to happen with plantations as not only the price, but also overall demand of specialty coffees is taking a hit as the specialty shops are still locked down. This affects large scale, commercial farms, as well as the specialized and everything in between. It seems to be the perfect storm.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Currently my main concern is both the quality and quantity of future harvests. After several years of bad prices, quality will inevitably suffer. If a small producer sells below his production cost, he will look forward to cut costs in fertilizing, soil tests, among others. Quality will also inevitably drop as a result.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">In my perception, we are on the second year of low prices, so the pressure is going up and this is now evident. Some producers start sacrificing quality as a result.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">How is the coffee industry changing? What are the changes coffee industry has seen in the few decades?</span></strong><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">There is a lot of intention to try new things, if you compare today´s mindset of a coffee producer with regards to the past. Tradition is a very interesting aspect of what is now changing. What is tradition after all? Why is it so hard to break and to do otherwise? Drifting away from tradition always implies risk. In most cases it is necessary and brings great progress. You always have to invest to get good results. Every achievement requires a potential first attempt that will fail.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">This is a very ample subject for discussion. This is something you can analyse from the “niche market” perspective. There are coffee sectors that are not subject to this price problem. &nbsp;There are “niches” where the quality is the defining aspect.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">As these niches have been developing, the end consumer has been able to appreciate these coffees that have clearly a different value and they dare to pay for new things.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">So, if you want to innovate, you must risk. And why would you risk the safe results you are used to achieve? Because the market is demanding it and is rewarding this risk. The market is rewarding quality for such cup profiles, and this new demand for quality enables farmers to have a budget to try new processes and techniques, to buy new machinery, get new varietals, to do more research in terms of fertilizing.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">It is always interesting to analyze tradition because it is a known way to get results. Hence, it is a safe bet. That’s why it’s probably so hard to leave tradition behind. But on the other hand, prices are not very attractive when it comes to a “normal” or “traditional” coffee. These are very interesting times we are living in as there is plenty of innovation going on. </span><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">What are the measures for producing best quality crop?</span></strong><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">There are several aspects to measure when it comes to producing great coffees.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">We try to keep our R&amp;D department busy. In broad terms, we are mainly monitoring of various data points for a number of varietals throughout the year, and we are also testing new processing methods during the harvest. We are constantly testing out new varietals to see how they work on our soils, altitudes and weather. We measure absolutely everything: soil composition, leaf composition, nutrients absorbed by the plants, nutrients that are lacking, amount of rain throughout the whole year. This kind of work will be done in a perpetual way, forever.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">In regard to the plant productivity, we look forward to measure production density. How do we do this? We measure the growth of the plant in a specific time span, the height of the first productive branch, how many productive branches do we have at 1 meter above the ground, amount of productive branches 2 meters above the ground. Then we start analyzing productive points in a particular branch, the distance between them, how many beans are we getting on that particular production point. After collecting the data, we analyze the results to determine if this particular plant or varietal has a promising future in that particular plantation. After all of this, the coffee itself is cupped and evaluated at the quality level in order to determine if it is a varietal of interest for our plantation.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Sometimes we face certain dilemmas with new varietals, because we don´t really know how they will react under certain circumstances. So we run parallel tests in order to measure our results more objectively.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">What are the various checkpoints when it comes to storage?</span></strong><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">After processing the coffee, we check: humidity levels, yields of the crop, visual aspect of the beans and cupping aspects (attributes/defects in the cup). Depending on the outcome, we determine whether the coffee has a potential to be sold as specialty or to be sold as conventional. Sampling is what makes all our lots 100% traceable.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Once the coffee is determined as specialty according to their optimal humidity content, we let them rest in Ecotact bags until we are ready to hull it.&nbsp; This helps the coffee to stabilize and settle into its fullest potential. This also allows us to offer the coffees and rest assured the quality will remain well stored until we are ready to ship.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">In many ways, the Ecotact bag buys you longer time! Not only with cup quality preservation but also with keeping the coffee’s ideal visual aspect too.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">What are the factors that should determine the type of packaging?</span></strong><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">The type of coffee determines the type of packaging in my opinion. High quality coffees benefit from protection before processing as the Ecotact bag provides for a perfect barrier for humidity changes, and this allows the coffee to settle slowly and without interruptions before it gets finally processed and shipped.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">For exports: I adapt to my client´s needs. We are working as usual in the 69 kg form, but also in 30-35 kg form (more and more often now). There is also occasional demand for vacuum packaging when it comes to top quality coffees.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">I usually recommend Vacuum for coffees that will be consumed slowly or is planned for long term storage. Ecotact bags for “shorter” term consumption up to a full year with great results in preservation of cup quality and overall physical aspect.&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">What impact will the coffee industry see because of pandemic COVID 19 and lockdown?</span></strong><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">It will change the way in which we reach the end consumer. There will be readjustments in the way we drink coffee, especially at home. Coffee drinking is being reinvented for a lot of people.</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">As people are having less access to the cafes on the street, they find themselves in the position to have to drink it at home. People are now grinding at home, there are several models of home roasters being more accessible for everyone. Coffee drinkers are preparing more V60s and other pour-over methods.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Street cafes and small roasters are being affected by this crisis. Many of these small coffee shops are now doing mostly home deliveries of 1 lb of fresh roasted coffees. Other bigger companies that sell at supermarkets seem to be a little less affected.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">In these uncertain times, social distancing is also disrupting the social aspect of meeting in a coffee shop and drinking coffee together. This part is a bit unfortunate too.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">How hermetic packaging is going to help in this grave situation?</span></strong><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Ecotact buys me more time! Hermetic packaging is what will keep my coffee fresh as long as I need to keep it stored: be it in my Guatemalan warehouse or in the US warehouse (it happens!).</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">We have found great results using the Ecotact bags in unorthodox ways at the various steps along the coffee supply chain. Whether it is for origin parchment storage, or for shipping and storing the green beans, we use Ecotact to ensure and prolong the overall shelf life of our coffees while keeping their high quality intact for our customers to enjoy all over the world.</span></p>', '2020-04-13', '2021-05-10 14:17:53', '2021-06-22 08:16:48'),
(20, '2', '10', 'Opiniones de Samuel Coto Sobre el Sector', '<p><strong>&iquest;Cu&aacute;l es el escenario global de la plantaci&oacute;n de caf&eacute;?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">En t&eacute;rminos generales, el precio del caf&eacute; sigue siendo el mayor desaf&iacute;o. Sin embargo, esto afecta a distintos tipos de productores de manera diferente. Con la amenaza de COVID 19 es dif&iacute;cil saber exactamente qu&eacute; va a pasar con las plantaciones, ya que no s&oacute;lo el precio, sino tambi&eacute;n la demanda general de caf&eacute;s especiales est&aacute; sufriendo un golpe, ya que las tiendas especializadas siguen cerradas. Esto afecta a las explotaciones comerciales a gran escala, as&iacute; como a las especializadas y a todo lo que est&aacute; en medio. Parece ser la tormenta perfecta.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Actualmente mi principal preocupaci&oacute;n es tanto la calidad como la cantidad de las futuras cosechas. Tras varios a&ntilde;os de malos precios, la calidad se ver&aacute; inevitablemente afectada. Si un peque&ntilde;o productor vende por debajo de su coste de producci&oacute;n, buscar&aacute; recortar costes en fertilizaci&oacute;n, pruebas de suelo, entre otros. En consecuencia, la calidad tambi&eacute;n descender&aacute; inevitablemente.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">En mi opini&oacute;n, estamos en el segundo a&ntilde;o de precios bajos, por lo que la presi&oacute;n est&aacute; subiendo y esto es ahora evidente. Algunos productores empiezan a sacrificar la calidad como resultado.</span></p>\r\n    <p><strong>&iquest;C&oacute;mo est&aacute; cambiando la industria del caf&eacute;? &iquest;Cu&aacute;les son los cambios que ha experimentado la industria del caf&eacute; en las &uacute;ltimas d&eacute;cadas?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hay mucha intenci&oacute;n de probar cosas nuevas, si se compara la mentalidad actual de un productor de caf&eacute; con respecto al pasado. La tradici&oacute;n es un aspecto muy interesante de lo que ahora est&aacute; cambiando. Despu&eacute;s de todo, &iquest;qu&eacute; es la tradici&oacute;n? &iquest;Por qu&eacute; es tan dif&iacute;cil romperla y hacer lo contrario? Alejarse de la tradici&oacute;n siempre implica un riesgo. En la mayor&iacute;a de los casos es necesario y supone un gran progreso. Siempre hay que invertir para obtener buenos resultados. Todo logro requiere un primer intento potencial que fracasar&aacute;.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Este es un tema muy amplio de debate. Es algo que se puede analizar desde la perspectiva del \"nicho de mercado\". Hay sectores del caf&eacute; que no est&aacute;n sujetos a este problema de precios.&nbsp; Hay \"nichos\" en los que la calidad es el aspecto definitorio.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A medida que estos nichos se han ido desarrollando, el consumidor final ha sabido apreciar estos caf&eacute;s que tienen claramente un valor diferente y se atreve a pagar por cosas nuevas.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As&iacute; que, si quieres innovar, debes arriesgar. &iquest;Y por qu&eacute; arriesgar los resultados seguros que est&aacute;s acostumbrado a conseguir? Porque el mercado lo est&aacute; exigiendo y est&aacute; premiando este riesgo. El mercado est&aacute; premiando la calidad para esos perfiles de copa, y esta nueva demanda de calidad permite a los agricultores tener un presupuesto para probar nuevos procesos y t&eacute;cnicas, para comprar nueva maquinaria, conseguir nuevas variedades, investigar m&aacute;s en t&eacute;rminos de fertilizaci&oacute;n.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Siempre es interesante analizar la tradici&oacute;n porque es una forma conocida de obtener resultados. Por lo tanto, es una apuesta segura. Por eso probablemente sea tan dif&iacute;cil dejar la tradici&oacute;n. Pero, por otro lado, los precios no son muy atractivos cuando se trata de un caf&eacute; \"normal\" o \"tradicional\". Son tiempos muy interesantes los que vivimos, ya que se est&aacute; innovando mucho.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n    <p><strong>&iquest;Cu&aacute;les son las medidas para producir una cosecha de la mejor calidad?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hay varios aspectos que medir cuando se trata de producir grandes caf&eacute;s.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Intentamos mantener ocupado nuestro departamento de I+D. A grandes rasgos, controlamos principalmente varios puntos de datos para una serie de varietales a lo largo del a&ntilde;o, y tambi&eacute;n probamos nuevos m&eacute;todos de procesamiento durante la cosecha. Probamos constantemente nuevas variedades para ver c&oacute;mo funcionan en nuestros suelos, altitudes y climas. Medimos absolutamente todo: la composici&oacute;n del suelo, la composici&oacute;n de las hojas, los nutrientes que absorben las plantas, los que faltan, la cantidad de lluvia durante todo el a&ntilde;o. Este tipo de trabajo se har&aacute; de forma perpetua, para siempre.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">En cuanto a la productividad de la planta, buscamos medir la densidad de producci&oacute;n. &iquest;C&oacute;mo lo hacemos? Medimos el crecimiento de la planta en un lapso de tiempo determinado, la altura de la primera rama productiva, cu&aacute;ntas ramas productivas tenemos a 1 metro del suelo, cantidad de ramas productivas a 2 metros del suelo. A continuaci&oacute;n, empezamos a analizar los puntos productivos de una rama concreta, la distancia entre ellos, cu&aacute;ntos granos estamos obteniendo en ese punto productivo concreto. Despu&eacute;s de recopilar los datos, analizamos los resultados para determinar si esa planta o variedad en particular tiene un futuro prometedor en esa plantaci&oacute;n concreta. Despu&eacute;s de todo esto, el caf&eacute; en s&iacute; es catado y evaluado a nivel de calidad para determinar si es una variedad de inter&eacute;s para nuestra plantaci&oacute;n.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">A veces nos enfrentamos a ciertos dilemas con las nuevas variedades, porque no sabemos realmente c&oacute;mo van a reaccionar en determinadas circunstancias. As&iacute; que realizamos pruebas paralelas para medir nuestros resultados de forma m&aacute;s objetiva.</span></p>\r\n    <p><strong>&iquest;Cu&aacute;les son los distintos puntos de control a la hora de almacenar?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Despu&eacute;s de procesar el caf&eacute;, comprobamos: los niveles de humedad, el rendimiento de la cosecha, el aspecto visual de los granos y los aspectos de la cata (atributos/defectos en la taza). Dependiendo del resultado, determinamos si el caf&eacute; tiene potencial para ser vendido como especial o para ser vendido como convencional. El muestreo es lo que hace que todos nuestros lotes sean 100% trazables.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Una vez que el caf&eacute; se determina como especial seg&uacute;n su contenido &oacute;ptimo de humedad, lo dejamos reposar en sacos Ecotact hasta que estamos listos para descascararlo.&nbsp; Esto ayuda a que el caf&eacute; se estabilice y se asiente en su m&aacute;ximo potencial. Esto tambi&eacute;n nos permite ofrecer los caf&eacute;s y tener la seguridad de que la calidad se mantendr&aacute; bien almacenada hasta que estemos listos para el env&iacute;o.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">En muchos sentidos, la bolsa Ecotact le permite ganar tiempo. No s&oacute;lo con la conservaci&oacute;n de la calidad de la taza, sino tambi&eacute;n con el mantenimiento del aspecto visual ideal del caf&eacute;.</span></p>\r\n    <p><strong>&iquest;Cu&aacute;les son los factores que deben determinar el tipo de envase?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">En mi opini&oacute;n, el tipo de caf&eacute; determina el tipo de envase. Los caf&eacute;s de alta calidad se benefician de la protecci&oacute;n antes del procesamiento, ya que la bolsa Ecotact proporciona una barrera perfecta para los cambios de humedad, y esto permite que el caf&eacute; se asiente lentamente y sin interrupciones antes de ser finalmente procesado y enviado.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Para las exportaciones: Me adapto a las necesidades de mis clientes. Trabajamos como siempre en el formato de 69 kg, pero tambi&eacute;n en el de 30-35 kg (cada vez m&aacute;s a menudo). Tambi&eacute;n hay una demanda ocasional de envasado al vac&iacute;o cuando se trata de caf&eacute;s de alta calidad.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Suelo recomendar el vac&iacute;o para caf&eacute;s que se van a consumir lentamente o que est&aacute; previsto almacenar a largo plazo. Las bolsas Ecotact para el consumo a \"corto\" plazo hasta un a&ntilde;o completo con grandes resultados en la preservaci&oacute;n de la calidad de la taza y el aspecto f&iacute;sico general.</span></p>\r\n    <p><strong>&iquest;Qu&eacute; impacto tendr&aacute; la industria del caf&eacute; a causa de la pandemia COVID 19 y el bloqueo?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cambiar&aacute; la forma de llegar al consumidor final. Habr&aacute; reajustes en la forma de beber caf&eacute;, especialmente en casa. El consumo de caf&eacute; se est&aacute; reinventando para mucha gente.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Como la gente tiene menos acceso a los caf&eacute;s de la calle, se encuentra en la situaci&oacute;n de tener que beberlo en casa. La gente ahora muele en casa, hay varios modelos de tostadores caseros que son m&aacute;s accesibles para todos. Los consumidores de caf&eacute; preparan m&aacute;s V60 y otros m&eacute;todos de vertido.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Los caf&eacute;s de la calle y los peque&ntilde;os tostadores se est&aacute;n viendo afectados por esta crisis. Muchas de estas peque&ntilde;as cafeter&iacute;as est&aacute;n haciendo ahora principalmente entregas a domicilio de 1 libra de caf&eacute;s reci&eacute;n tostados. Otras empresas m&aacute;s grandes que venden en supermercados parecen estar un poco menos afectadas.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">En estos tiempos de incertidumbre, el distanciamiento social tambi&eacute;n est&aacute; perturbando el aspecto social de reunirse en una cafeter&iacute;a y tomar caf&eacute; juntos. Esta parte tambi&eacute;n es un poco desafortunada.</span></p>\r\n    <p><strong>&iquest;C&oacute;mo van a ayudar los envases herm&eacute;ticos en esta grave situaci&oacute;n?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">&iexcl;Ecotact me hace ganar tiempo! El envase herm&eacute;tico es lo que mantendr&aacute; mi caf&eacute; fresco todo el tiempo que necesite tenerlo almacenado: ya sea en mi almac&eacute;n de Guatemala o en el de EE.UU. (&iexcl;suele ocurrir!).</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hemos encontrado grandes resultados utilizando las bolsas Ecotact de formas poco ortodoxas en las distintas etapas de la cadena de suministro del caf&eacute;. Ya sea para el almacenamiento en pergamino de origen, o para el env&iacute;o y almacenamiento de los granos verdes, utilizamos Ecotact para asegurar y prolongar la vida &uacute;til general de nuestros caf&eacute;s, manteniendo su alta calidad intacta para que nuestros clientes la disfruten en todo el mundo.</span></p>', '2020-04-13', '2021-05-10 14:17:53', '2021-06-22 08:16:48'),
(21, '1', '11', 'Words from Asia’s First Lady of Coffee', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">What are the milestones achieved by India after liberalisation of the Indian coffee market in 1995?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Focus on quality of coffee during processing and marketing has hugely increased. Indian coffee farmers are now travelling overseas and participating in coffee conferences and exhibitions to market their coffee. Market linkages have been established, especially in relationship marketing. There has been significant branding of Indian coffees as well, making the coffee world note that India produces excellent Arabica and Robusta coffees.</span></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">How is the green coffee industry changing?</span><br></strong><br><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Traceability and certification are very important factors in the international coffee market.</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Block chain marketing is now taking place with direct sales between buyer and seller.</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Today green coffee is also getting brewed in different ways, thereby bringing in innovation and technology in agricultural practices and in processing techniques. This ensures that the quality of green beans will be so developed that they can be utilised to brew coffee through different brewing methodologies. Processing variants in the preparation of green beans have taken the centre stage.</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Cafes are opening their doors in producing origins such as in China and Vietnam. Thus they are helping in increasing the consumption of coffee in the coffee producing countries and changing, to an extent, the green coffee industry which had been catering mainly to the coffee consuming countries in the past.</span><br><br></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">What’s the role of India in the global coffee market?</span></strong></p><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">India plays a fairly important role in the espresso market with roasters who roast for espresso blends, finding that our Indian coffees can provide a great base for their espresso blends.</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Preparation of microlots, through variation in processing techniques, has helped in providing a basket of flavours to the global coffee market.</span><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">﻿</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">At present Robusta coffee is 40% of the world market and Indian Robusta is rated as a high quality Robusta in the international market, with premium prices being paid for our quality Robusta coffees.</span><br><br><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">How big is the export market for Indian coffee?</span></strong><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">75% of our coffee is exported.</span><br><br><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">What’s the importance of packaging when it comes to coffee export?</span></strong><br><br><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Packaging is a very crucial aspect for exports of both green and roasted coffees. In case of green coffee, the most important requirement is to preserve the intrinsic quality of the green coffee beans, especially in protecting and ensuring the moisture content in the coffee beans, to ensure shelf-life and retention of quality. In the case of roasted and ground coffee, it is important to preserve the aromatics and flavours of the coffee, which necessitates good packaging material.</span><br><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Today, hermetically sealed bags are utilised to pack green coffee beans to preserve the intrinsic quality of the green beans.</span><br></p>', '2019-11-28', '2021-05-10 14:19:00', '2021-06-22 08:17:19'),
(22, '2', '11', 'Palabras de La Primera Dama Del Café de Asia', '<p><strong>&iquest;Cu&aacute;les son los hitos alcanzados por la India tras la liberalizaci&oacute;n del mercado indio del caf&eacute; en 1995?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">La atenci&oacute;n a la calidad del caf&eacute; durante el procesamiento y la comercializaci&oacute;n ha aumentado enormemente. Los caficultores indios viajan ahora al extranjero y participan en conferencias y exposiciones de caf&eacute; para comercializarlo. Se han establecido v&iacute;nculos con el mercado, especialmente en lo que respecta a la comercializaci&oacute;n de relaciones. Tambi&eacute;n se ha producido una importante creaci&oacute;n de marca de los caf&eacute;s indios, lo que ha hecho que el mundo del caf&eacute; se d&eacute; cuenta de que la India produce excelentes caf&eacute;s Ar&aacute;bica y Robusta.</span></p>\r\n    <p><strong>&iquest;C&oacute;mo est&aacute; cambiando la industria del caf&eacute; verde?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">La trazabilidad y la certificaci&oacute;n son factores muy importantes en el mercado internacional del caf&eacute;.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">El mercadeo en Block Chain se est&aacute; llevando a cabo con ventas directas entre el comprador y el vendedor.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hoy en d&iacute;a, el caf&eacute; verde tambi&eacute;n se prepara de diferentes maneras, lo que aporta innovaci&oacute;n y tecnolog&iacute;a en las pr&aacute;cticas agr&iacute;colas y en las t&eacute;cnicas de procesamiento. Esto garantiza que la calidad de los granos verdes se desarrolle de tal manera que puedan utilizarse para preparar el caf&eacute; mediante diferentes metodolog&iacute;as de elaboraci&oacute;n. Las variantes de procesamiento en la preparaci&oacute;n de los granos verdes han pasado a primer plano.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Los caf&eacute;s est&aacute;n abriendo sus puertas en or&iacute;genes productores como en China y Vietnam. De este modo, est&aacute;n contribuyendo a aumentar el consumo de caf&eacute; en los pa&iacute;ses productores y a cambiar, en cierta medida, la industria del caf&eacute; verde, que en el pasado abastec&iacute;a principalmente a los pa&iacute;ses consumidores de caf&eacute;.</span></p>\r\n    <p><strong>&iquest;Cu&aacute;l es el papel de la India en el mercado mundial del caf&eacute;?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">La India desempe&ntilde;a un papel bastante importante en el mercado del espresso, ya que los tostadores que tuestan para las mezclas de espresso descubren que nuestros caf&eacute;s indios pueden proporcionar una gran base para sus mezclas de espresso.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">La preparaci&oacute;n de micro-lotes, mediante la variaci&oacute;n de las t&eacute;cnicas de elaboraci&oacute;n, ha contribuido a proporcionar una cesta de sabores al mercado mundial del caf&eacute;.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">En la actualidad, el caf&eacute; Robusta representa el 40% del mercado mundial y el Robusta indio est&aacute; considerado como un Robusta de alta calidad en el mercado internacional, y se pagan precios superiores por nuestros caf&eacute;s Robusta de calidad.</span></p>\r\n    <p><strong>&iquest;Qu&eacute; tama&ntilde;o tiene el mercado de exportaci&oacute;n del caf&eacute; indio?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">El 75% de nuestro caf&eacute; se exporta.</span></p>\r\n    <p><strong>&iquest;Qu&eacute; importancia tiene el envasado en la exportaci&oacute;n de caf&eacute;?</strong></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">El envasado es un aspecto muy crucial para las exportaciones tanto de caf&eacute; verde como de caf&eacute; tostado. En el caso del caf&eacute; verde, el requisito m&aacute;s importante es preservar la calidad intr&iacute;nseca de los granos de caf&eacute; verde, especialmente para proteger y garantizar el contenido de humedad en los granos de caf&eacute;, para asegurar la vida &uacute;til y la retenci&oacute;n de la calidad. En el caso del caf&eacute; tostado y molido, es importante preservar los aromas y sabores del caf&eacute;, lo que requiere un buen material de envasado.</span></p>\r\n    <p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hoy en d&iacute;a, se utilizan empaques herm&eacute;ticos para envasar los granos de caf&eacute; verde con el fin de preservar su calidad intr&iacute;nseca.</span></p>', '2019-11-28', '2021-05-10 14:19:00', '2021-06-22 08:17:19'),
(23, '1', '12', '5 Ways Through Which 9 Layer Packaging Keeps the Quality of Food Grains Intact', '<p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Choosing the best packaging for your food grains is of utmost importance. A multi-layered hermetic packaging</span><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">&nbsp;</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">ensures that the grains are fresh for longer which directly impacts the taste of the grains or beans. While selecting the right packaging, always keep in mind that the packaging must not only help in preserving but also protecting the grains from external influences. Listed below are 5 ways in which 9 layer hermetic packaging prevents deterioration in the quality of the grains.</span></p><ol style=\"margin: 23px 0px 34px 40px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: inherit; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; list-style: none; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); counter-reset: item 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Ensures safe moisture level: If the grains are too moist, there is a chance that they will get spoilt in storage and if they are too dry, then the reduced weight will lead to the reduction of its value. &nbsp;The 9 layer hermetic packaging helps in retaining perfect moisture content.</span></li><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Protects from external moisture: When moisture gets into the grains, molds and insects appear. This packaging ensures that the grains are protected from moisture damage.</span></li><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Has high temperature tolerance: High temperatures during storage or transportation process may trigger evaporation of the residual moisture from the grains during day time. This is followed by condensation and re-absorption of moisture at night. Multi-layered hermetic packaging on the contrary has high temperature tolerance&nbsp; (-30 to 90 degree centigrade)</span></li><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Locks in aroma and maintains flavour: Sampling of food grains, especially green coffee by traders, roasters and producers is one of the most critical exercises. Most of the time, stakeholders neglect this fact by choosing sub-standard packaging which results in lower prices. But 9 layer hermetic packaging ensures that coffee remains in farm fresh condition with optimum level of moisture and aroma.</span></li><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 28px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; position: relative;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">&nbsp;Protects sensitive food and vitamin content: Each grain type is different. Hermetic solutions manufactured using special researched technology to preserve the natural freshness of the farms in warehouses and during its transport, without the use of pesticide &amp; insecticide, help in keeping various grains unharmed post-harvest.</span></li></ol><p style=\"margin-bottom: 12px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; font-size: 14px; line-height: 28px; font-family: Merriweather, serif; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px;\">Ecotact’s 9-layer hermetic packaging solutions are the ultimate solutions for packaging and storing your food grains, especially green coffee. They are extremely strong and have high oxygen and moisture barrier properties that seal freshness throughout the supply chain. Also, they are eco-friendly and 100% recyclable.</span></p>', '2019-08-09', '2021-05-10 14:20:02', '2021-06-22 08:26:24');
