(26, '2', '13', 'Ecotact Presenta Las Nuevas Bolsas De Embalaje Herméticas Ecológicas, Especialmente Diseñadas Con Triple Protección Para Pequeños Tostadores, Tostadores Doméstico Y Baristas.', '<p>Si usted es un tostador de peque&ntilde;a escala, tostador dom&eacute;stico o barista, las nuevas Troiseal Bags han sido desarrolladas exclusivamente para usted, teniendo en cuenta sus necesidades de almacenamiento. Sabemos exactamente lo que se necesita para conservar el caf&eacute; verde reci&eacute;n cultivado a mano y con mucha pasi&oacute;n.</p>\r\n<p><strong>&iquest;Qu&eacute; es una Bolsa con triple sello?</strong></p>\r\n<p>La bolsa Ecotact Troiseal tiene tres sellos secuenciales. \"Tri\" etimol&oacute;gicamente significa tres y, como sugiere el nombre, se puede sellar a la perfecci&oacute;n, y adem&aacute;s garantiza que la humedad no ingrese ni altere el contenido.</p>\r\n<p><strong>&iquest;Por qu&eacute; utilizar las bolsas con Triple Sello? </strong></p>\r\n<p>Los beneficios de adquirir las bolsas con triple protecci&oacute;n son:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Han sido dise&ntilde;adas usando 9 capas de empaque herm&eacute;tico.</li>\r\n<li>Es completamente a prueba de manipulaciones. Han sido dise&ntilde;adas para proteger el contenido.</li>\r\n<li>Tambi&eacute;n se puede utilizar para almacenar ma&iacute;z, cebada, panela y cacao.</li>\r\n<li>Las bolsas son transparentes permitir una clara visibilidad del contenido.</li>\r\n<li>Son 100% reciclables y reutilizables, teniendo en consideraci&oacute;n el cuidado del medio ambiente ecol&oacute;gico.</li>\r\n<li>Tiene 03 cierres secuenciales adhesivos de varias capas y permiten volver a sellar f&aacute;cilmente.</li>\r\n<li>Tienen un asa en la parte superior para levantar y transportar f&aacute;cilmente.</li>\r\n<li>Precios muy competitivos debido a la amplia demanda del producto.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Para conocer m&aacute;s haz <a href=\"https://www.ecotactbags.com/eco-product/packaging/troiseal-bags\">click</a> aqu&iacute;:</p>\r\n<p>Adem&aacute;s de todas las ventajas mencionadas anteriormente, las bolsas de triple sellado est&aacute;n dise&ntilde;adas para ser completamente ecol&oacute;gicas para continuar el lema principal de Ecotact, que es preservar el medio ambiente para un futuro sostenible. Es ahora m&aacute;s que nunca que nuestro planeta necesita que demos un paso adelante y tomemos medidas para limpiar el desastre que la humanidad ha causado como resultado de la irresponsabilidad y negligencia. A&uacute;n queda mucho por hacer para devolver el equilibrio a nuestro ecosistema. Para obtener m&aacute;s informaci&oacute;n, deje un comentario a continuaci&oacute;n y nuestro equipo se comunicar&aacute; con usted pronto.</p>', '2021-05-29', '2021-06-10 07:36:29', '2021-07-13 07:08:29'),
(27, '1', '14', 'Home Coffee Roasting - Storing your Green coffee beans', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:underline;-webkit-text-decoration-skip:none;text-decoration-skip-ink:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">“Home Coffee Roasting - Storing your Green coffee beans”.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:underline;-webkit-text-decoration-skip:none;text-decoration-skip-ink:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Roboto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">It is not unknown that high quality green coffee beans and brewing those with precision is the secret to an aroma-filled ‘cup of joe’. The process begins right from its inception and continues with the packaging and </span><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Roboto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">storage of the green coffee beans</span><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Roboto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">. When you are passionate about what you create but don’t have the perfect means to preserve it, it can be extremely infuriating. Therefore, it is quintessential for roasters to pay careful attention to the quality of green beans, cupping multiple samples, then identify the ideal roast profile, trying several options to discover how to best bring out the coffee’s flavors and identify the best storage system for your coffee. Storage, if not perfected, can be the biggest pain area for home roasters who believe in quality control.</span></p><p><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><br></b></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Roboto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Green coffee has a shelf life of up to a year. Roasted coffee, on the other hand, is notorious for fading in weeks. It is the roasting process that develops the flavors and aromatic notes that we often associate coffee with – be they chocolate, caramel, or floral ones. But as the coffee beans transform sensorially, their chemical composition changes too.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;padding:0pt 0pt 18pt 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Roboto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Your roasted coffee is vulnerable to multiple elements: light, heat, moisture, and most of all, oxygen. Good storage should maintain the coffee’s freshness, preserving its characteristics for as long as possible, so that your customers get to enjoy it at its best.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;padding:0pt 0pt 18pt 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Roboto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Preserving green coffee beans </span><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Roboto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">can be a task for small home roasters who have storage or space constraints. While there are different views on whether or not coffee should be frozen or refrigerated.</span><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Roboto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Awareness about the right solution for </span><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Roboto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">storing and packaging your passionately grown green coffee beans </span><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Roboto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">and roasting them with precision</span><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Roboto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Roboto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">will give you an edge over your competitors.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Roboto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Being porous, coffee beans are hygroscopic. In simpler terms, coffee beans tend to absorb the fragrance of anything that it comes in contact with. So, if you store flowers along with loosely kept coffee beans, it will absorb the smell of the flower easily. In order to retain the authentic freshness of aroma which it originally has, the coffee beans need to be preserved well. A good packaging company of coffee beans should consider the following threats in mind while manufacturing the storage packets.&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Roboto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br></span></p><ol style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal;font-size:13.999999999999998pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.3800000000000001;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size: 13pt; font-family: Roboto; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; fo