(143, '1', '55', 'Guatemalan coffee: Marking its authenticity since the 18th century', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">What makes Guatemala famous for its coffee?</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Guatemala is known to be the Mecca for coffee farmers. The coffee in the Guatemala region is cultivated at an altitude of about 5000 feet, which provides a distinctive robust flavor to the coffee beans.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">The coffee beans produced on the southern slopes of the volcanic regions are always in demand. The Guatemalan highlands give birth to plenty of microclimates that allow perfect conditions for great coffee to be developed. Its fertile region is very unique with a mild subtropical climate and witnesses a nutrient-rich volcanic soil thereby making the perfect environment for producing one of the most flavorful coffee beans in the world.&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;padding:0pt 0pt 8pt 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Guatemalan coffee is a star performer because of how its produced and processed. With the right environmental conditions and a major focus on the nurturing phase, it is widely spread in about 20 different departments in Guatemala.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;padding:0pt 0pt 8pt 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Guatemala’s highly elevated lands, diverse microclimates, unvarying rainfall patterns, and seamless cultivation and processing, make for a variety of distinctive types of Guatemalan coffee.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Understanding the variety and flavor of Guatemalan coffee</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">According to Stephane Cuchet from Ecotact, Guatemala, “ Each coffee bean will give off a different note based on how the coffee beans are processed. The elegant washed coffee is the “classical Guatemalan coffee cup”. This cup will usually have good acidity, a round body, and chocolate notes. Let’s take a deeper look at the properties of Guatemala coffee beans.</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">If the beans are washed, they would contain a good acidity level with a rounded body and chocolatey notes.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">If the beans are naturally processed, then they are found to have a fruity profile with a natural scent.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">In case the processing is anaerobic, the beans would possess strong notes of blueberries, citric fruits and sweet mango flavors.</span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">And if the beans have undergone honey processing, they are found in heavily designed bodies and contain a lot of sweetness in them.</span></p></li></ul><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">What makes it different from other coffee</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">What makes Guatemalan coffee unique is the conditions in which it is farmed. The plantation\'s altitude normally ranges between 1200 - 2000 meters above sea level in Guatemala.&nbsp;</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Along with this, there is plenty of water found on the coffee farms which makes it feasible to perform the classic wash profile. These 2 factors offer distinctively unique attributes to the coffee beans.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\">&nbsp;</p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Best 3 Guatemalan Coffee Beans</span></p><p><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-4edbaf78-7fff-242c-276d-fde223a1d335\"><br></b></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;padding:0pt 0pt 11pt 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Antigua Santa Barbara</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"> symbolises true Central American coffee.</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">These coffee beans are meant for those who enjoy their coffee with a chocolatey twist and notes of rich nutty flavors with creaminess. The exotic acidity and candy-like sweetness offer the perfect balance to the flavor of these beans. It leaves a sweet aftertaste. These beans produce an intense aroma that is known to leave a long-lasting fragrance.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;padding:0pt 0pt 11pt 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Organic Huehuetenango</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"> is all about balancing notes with its low-acidity level.</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">These beans are for those who love a cup of rich and smooth coffee with a lip-smacking caramel-like sweetness. It comes with notes of fruitiness and mild chocolatey flavor making it a balanced and bright coffee bean. The aftertaste here is rather light and crisp.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;padding:0pt 0pt 11pt 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">San Marcos</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"> is everything you can expect from a nut-oriented coffee flavor, fragrance and aftertaste.</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br></span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#333333;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">The coffee beans feel smooth on the taste buds and light on the stomach. The sweetness and acidity in the coffee are dominated by the nutty flavor along with floral notes. This makes the coffee amplified by a nice nutty fragrance, aroma, taste and aftertaste as well!</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Some lesser-known facts about Guatemala and its special coffee beans</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p><ul style=\"margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-inline-start:48px;\"><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">The Guatemalan coffee sector is gigantic in the present day and generates about 40% of total agricultural export and a quarter of its population is invested in producing about 3.5 million bags of Guatemala coffee every year.</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">In the present-day scenario, 98% of coffee is shade grown where Arabica production is found to be fully washed but in recent times, natural and honey methods are now being recognized for yielding excellent results too. </span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#262626;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Different zones in the country are now moving towards advanced processing practices and the farmers are placed at the forefront of greenhouse drying methodologies.</span><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\"><br><br></span></p></li><li dir=\"ltr\" style=\"list-style-type:disc;font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;\" aria-level=\"1\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;background-color:#ffffff;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:8pt;\" role=\"presentation\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">High-altitude, abundant rainfall and mineral-rich soils help make this coffee bean a stellar crop. With approximately 300 distinctive microclimates, these coffee beans display an array of flavors for each and every one!</span></p></li></ul><p><b style=\"font-weight:normal;\"><br></b></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt;font-family:Raleway,sans-serif;color:#202124;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Ecotact’s hermetically sealed bags are designed to keep the richness and aroma of the coffee intact by blocking out moisture completely. With constant efforts to preserve the quality of coffee beans, people around the world can relish a cup of freshly brewed Guatemalan coffee without compromising on its true flavors.</span></p><p><br></p>', 'Wednesday November 23, 2022', '2022-11-23 12:41:19', '2022-11-23 12:41:19'),
(144, '2', '55', NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-11-23 12:41:19', '2022-11-23 12:41:19');
INSERT INTO `language__blogs` (`id`, `language_id`, `blog_id`, `title`, `desc`, `date`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(145, '1', '56', 'Changing the coffee culture through sustainable steps', '<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><font color=\"#000000\">The last several decades have seen a steady increase in the consumption of coffee, penetrating into new markets thereby attracting a bigger target group. Consequently, the rise in demand has led to several changes in the coffee industry, be it the process of harvesting or roasting. As per the trend, the consumption level is predicted to double by 2050 and as a result, there is an unexpected increase in waste; both organic and inorganic.</font></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-64395152-7fff-0fe3-de37-c42725123fd0\"><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><font color=\"#000000\">Sustainability is now turning out to be a key element within the coffee industry and a vast majority of roasters and small businesses are working towards reducing organic waste by transforming it into useful resources thereby contributing to the circular economy.&nbsp;</font></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-2863e856-7fff-353c-bfde-2c552da06af4\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\">Circular economy in Coffee Production</font></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><font color=\"#000000\">When roasters attempt to reuse the waste produced in coffee production when used efficiently, this waste can boost the fertility of coffee farms and reduce the use of chemicals for field activities. It can also help in protecting the environment and ensuring a safer way of working. Ultimately, when sustainability is the key aim, then it automatically opens up business opportunities for coffee producers and everyone else in the value chain.</font></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><font color=\"#000000\">Let us understand how coffee roasters can save the community, soil, and the overall environment via processes like composting.</font></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14.6667px; font-weight: 700;\">Composting as a source of prevention for landfills and greenhouse gas emissions</span><font color=\"#000000\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-00b818a2-7fff-15cb-2019-96ca752bb1c5\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"> </span></span><br></font></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-4a2bae2c-7fff-e389-32c3-641d82765c40\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\">When the matter in landfills breaks down anaerobically, it releases harmful greenhouse gases such as methane which is directly released into the atmosphere and contributes to global warming. But composting as a method is similar to natural decomposition which allows organic waste to break down with oxygen. Hence, it reduces overall waste that is disposed of in landfills and reduces the production of greenhouse gases. While roasting coffee is an efficient process by itself, as per a study, the process of roasting, packaging, and distribution of coffee accounts for approximately 15% of the total footprint journey from the crop to cup.</font></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-4a2bae2c-7fff-e389-32c3-641d82765c40\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-4a2bae2c-7fff-e389-32c3-641d82765c40\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ade6de00-7fff-5847-9665-dbf7da3059a5\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 14.6667px;\">Strengthens</span><font color=\"#000000\"> soil and promotes healthy plant growth</font></span></span></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-4a2bae2c-7fff-e389-32c3-641d82765c40\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ade6de00-7fff-5847-9665-dbf7da3059a5\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-47f805c5-7fff-77c8-eb8f-7f8b0ab2d46c\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\">Composting also helps in improving the quality of soil making it more suitable for production by adding organic matter to it. When the organic content increases, the soil is able to absorb and retain water, nutrients and air which is helpful to the plant ecosystem.</font></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-4a2bae2c-7fff-e389-32c3-641d82765c40\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ade6de00-7fff-5847-9665-dbf7da3059a5\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-47f805c5-7fff-77c8-eb8f-7f8b0ab2d46c\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-4a2bae2c-7fff-e389-32c3-641d82765c40\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ade6de00-7fff-5847-9665-dbf7da3059a5\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-47f805c5-7fff-77c8-eb8f-7f8b0ab2d46c\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-53164c21-7fff-fec4-4a1a-b7cf678a0515\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\">Reduces the use of pesticides and synthetic fertilizers</font></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-4a2bae2c-7fff-e389-32c3-641d82765c40\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ade6de00-7fff-5847-9665-dbf7da3059a5\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-47f805c5-7fff-77c8-eb8f-7f8b0ab2d46c\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-53164c21-7fff-fec4-4a1a-b7cf678a0515\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-a66f97eb-7fff-2eb5-e762-b0c1187e64d2\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\">When plants grow in compost-rich soil, they are naturally more resilient to pests and infections. The healthy bacteria present in the soil help fight off the attack of pests and diseases at the very initial stages which eliminates the need to use harmful toxicants. Since compost is helpful in the addition of nutrients to soil &amp; </font></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 14.6667px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">changing</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> the quality of soil, it reduces the need for any kind of fertilizer.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); background-color: transparent; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><br></span><span style=\"font-size: 14.6667px; white-space: pre-wrap; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Raleway, sans-serif;\">To understand how to be more sustainable, it is essential to consciously incorporate some practices like: </span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; white-space: pre-wrap; letter-spacing: -0.015em;\"><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-656bca7b-7fff-d00b-32fa-0631d7f61afa\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><font color=\"#000000\">Minimum use of energy for production</font></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-656bca7b-7fff-d00b-32fa-0631d7f61afa\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-860159b8-7fff-0ab6-b35f-b7dd29449c65\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\">It is important to have a clear estimate of what a batch size is and how heavy will the machinery serve in quality control. For roasters with bigger operations, regenerative thermal oxidizers (RTO) are a great way to check energy costs as it recycles the heat back into the roaster instead of releasing it into the atmosphere. Hence, when it comes to upgrading, picking an energy-efficient alternative will go a long way.</font></span></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-656bca7b-7fff-d00b-32fa-0631d7f61afa\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-860159b8-7fff-0ab6-b35f-b7dd29449c65\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></span></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-656bca7b-7fff-d00b-32fa-0631d7f61afa\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-860159b8-7fff-0ab6-b35f-b7dd29449c65\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ddc85262-7fff-49c8-554f-1b44597b7bde\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\">Composting the coffee grounds</font></span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-656bca7b-7fff-d00b-32fa-0631d7f61afa\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-860159b8-7fff-0ab6-b35f-b7dd29449c65\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ddc85262-7fff-49c8-554f-1b44597b7bde\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-e894c0ba-7fff-8141-279f-a02cab713ea0\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\">The amount of disposed waste that comes from the coffee grounds is massive. As per an article, most regions around the world dispose of around 75% of their grounds in a landfill. But due to improper management of the municipality waste, there is an issue with the composting process. Coffee grounds are infused with nutrients and the stored nitrogen is great for the garden soil. Roasters can incentivize customers for taking the coffee grounds and place the used filters in a can in order to send it away later.</font></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-656bca7b-7fff-d00b-32fa-0631d7f61afa\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-860159b8-7fff-0ab6-b35f-b7dd29449c65\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ddc85262-7fff-49c8-554f-1b44597b7bde\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-e894c0ba-7fff-8141-279f-a02cab713ea0\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-656bca7b-7fff-d00b-32fa-0631d7f61afa\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-860159b8-7fff-0ab6-b35f-b7dd29449c65\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ddc85262-7fff-49c8-554f-1b44597b7bde\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-e894c0ba-7fff-8141-279f-a02cab713ea0\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-039acb30-7fff-a3b3-e8c3-e9eebaa42097\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\">Using excess water as a technique</font></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-656bca7b-7fff-d00b-32fa-0631d7f61afa\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-860159b8-7fff-0ab6-b35f-b7dd29449c65\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ddc85262-7fff-49c8-554f-1b44597b7bde\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-e894c0ba-7fff-8141-279f-a02cab713ea0\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-039acb30-7fff-a3b3-e8c3-e9eebaa42097\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-deab2cfb-7fff-c2f7-2233-7321e1250297\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\">If there is one resource that is used from the scratch till the end, it’s water. Apart from the crops, water is used heavily in cleaning. One way to start is by utilizing the rinsed water, preventing back-flushing, by dumping the water into containers in order to reuse it to water your fields.</font></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-656bca7b-7fff-d00b-32fa-0631d7f61afa\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-860159b8-7fff-0ab6-b35f-b7dd29449c65\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ddc85262-7fff-49c8-554f-1b44597b7bde\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-e894c0ba-7fff-8141-279f-a02cab713ea0\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-039acb30-7fff-a3b3-e8c3-e9eebaa42097\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-deab2cfb-7fff-c2f7-2233-7321e1250297\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-656bca7b-7fff-d00b-32fa-0631d7f61afa\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-860159b8-7fff-0ab6-b35f-b7dd29449c65\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ddc85262-7fff-49c8-554f-1b44597b7bde\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-e894c0ba-7fff-8141-279f-a02cab713ea0\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-039acb30-7fff-a3b3-e8c3-e9eebaa42097\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-deab2cfb-7fff-c2f7-2233-7321e1250297\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-150cfd9f-7fff-136a-08ee-a1029d53181e\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\">Reusing and recycling the materials</font></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-656bca7b-7fff-d00b-32fa-0631d7f61afa\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-860159b8-7fff-0ab6-b35f-b7dd29449c65\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ddc85262-7fff-49c8-554f-1b44597b7bde\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-e894c0ba-7fff-8141-279f-a02cab713ea0\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-039acb30-7fff-a3b3-e8c3-e9eebaa42097\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-deab2cfb-7fff-c2f7-2233-7321e1250297\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-150cfd9f-7fff-136a-08ee-a1029d53181e\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-47f3fff5-7fff-4918-431d-d49a22203af1\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\">While recycling items once, there is still a considerable amount of environmental footprint. While the coffee industry has been constantly evolving by taking up compostable packaging, there is still a chance that the materials don’t break down to 100%. But by picking better quality materials in packaging and storage, Ecotact prioritizes biodegradability and recyclability as its prime principles.</font></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-656bca7b-7fff-d00b-32fa-0631d7f61afa\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-860159b8-7fff-0ab6-b35f-b7dd29449c65\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ddc85262-7fff-49c8-554f-1b44597b7bde\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-e894c0ba-7fff-8141-279f-a02cab713ea0\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-039acb30-7fff-a3b3-e8c3-e9eebaa42097\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-deab2cfb-7fff-c2f7-2233-7321e1250297\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-150cfd9f-7fff-136a-08ee-a1029d53181e\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><span style=\"font-weight:normal;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-47f3fff5-7fff-4918-431d-d49a22203af1\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Speaking of its diverse portfolio, Ecotact has come a long way by bringing the most effective packaging solutions. </span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Products such as Sterile vacuum-sealed bags, Multi-layered hermetic bags and Troiseal bags are made with recyclable and eco-friendly materials without compromising the aroma &amp; freshness of the coffee beans. </span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The Biome trays and the 2-in-1 Supergreen 40 storage bags are compostable and designed to ensure high reusability and easy disposal. </span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; white-space: pre-wrap;\">These products are specifically designed to be sustainable packaging solutions in the coffee industry.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><font color=\"#000000\"><br></font></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-dfee28f8-7fff-9520-434b-3835b700313d\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"><font color=\"#000000\">So, the premium quality coffee beans stored in hermetic bags will feel farm-fresh, throughout the journey. Along with this, there are certain solid wastes that can’t be avoided are chaff and burlap bags. But Ecotact has meticulously designed its bags without chaff and burlaps to make them ideal for use without the use of plastic. </font></span></span></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;text-align: justify;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"background-color: transparent; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Raleway, sans-serif; font-size: 11pt; white-space: pre-wrap; letter-spacing: -0.015em;\"><br></span></p>', 'Monday November 28, 2022', '2022-11-28 15:29:56', '2022-11-28 15:44:28'),
